Uses of IUserComponent in vidis.data
 

Classes in vidis.data that implement IUserComponent
 class AUserLink
          abstract user link represents a link by a user; module writers should use this class to write their own link
 class AUserNode
          abstract user node represents a node by a user; module writers should use this class to write their own node
 class AUserPacket
          abstract user packet represents a packet by a user; module writers should use this class to write their own packet
 

Uses of IUserComponent in vidis.data.mod
 

Subinterfaces of IUserComponent in vidis.data.mod
 interface IUserLink
          this interface defines a basic functionality for all user module links; anyway for implementation of a new link in a ne module, the class AUserLink should be used instead.
 interface IUserNode
          the interface for a module node; please keep in mind that you should use the abstract class AUserNode to implement new modules. there we implemented basic functionality in order to let the simulator work flawlessly together with the module.
 interface IUserPacket
          the interface for a packet in a user implemented module. just like links and nodes you should NOT use this interface to implement a new module, but use the abstract AUserPacket class instead as there we implemented already a lot of basic and vital functionality for the simulator!
 

Classes in vidis.data.mod that implement IUserComponent
 class AUserComponent
          implements basic operations that are needed by all user objects
